[30;1m228 | [0m[35mThis likely happens because you're using botocore which `does not support urllib3 2.0 yet[0m

[30;1m231 | [0m[35mwill install urllib3 1.26.x until botocore starts supporting urllib3 2.0.[0m
[30;1m232 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m41 | [0m[35m    the SO_REUSEADDR socket option having different semantics on Windows versus[0m
[30;1m42 | [0m[35m    Unix/Linux.  On Unix, you can't have two AF_INET SOCK_STREAM sockets bind,[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35m    listen and then accept connections on identical host/ports.  An EADDRINUSE[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35m    OSError will be raised at some point (depending on the platform and[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m    the order bind and listen were called on each socket).[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m    However, on Windows, if SO_REUSEADDR is set on the sockets, no EADDRINUSE[0m

[30;1m360 | [0m[35m-------------------[0m
[30;1m361 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m362 | [0m[35mIf you want to create a connection to a host over HTTPS which uses SNI, there[0m
[30;1m363 | [0m[35mare two places where the hostname is expected. It must be included in the Host[0m

[30;1m366 | [0m[35mchecked by urllib3.[0m

[30;1m392 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m162 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m- Use the top-level ``urllib3.request()`` function for smaller code examples. For more involved exam[0m
[30;1m164 | [0m[35m- Use double quotes for all strings. (Output, Declaration etc.)[0m
[30;1m165 | [0m[35m- Use keyword arguments everywhere except for method and url. (ie ``http.request("GET", "https://exa[0m
[30;1m166 | [0m[35m- Use HTTPS in URLs everywhere unless HTTP is needed.[0m

[30;1m180 | [0m[35m- Imports should be their own section separated from the rest of the example with a line of whitespa[0m
[30;1m181 | [0m[35m- Imports should minimized if possible. Use import urllib3 instead of from urllib3 import X. [0m
[30;1m182 | [0m[35m- Sort imports similarly to isort, standard library first and third-party (like urllib3) come after.[0m
[30;1m183 | [0m[35m- No whitespace is required between the sections as normally would be in case of isort.[0m
[30;1m184 | [0m[35m- Add print statements along with a comment below them showing the output, potentially compressed.[0m
